TERMS OF SERVICE
Last Updated: July 8, 2025

By using the UploadNotifier Discord Bot ("the Bot"), you agree to the following terms of service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Bot.

1. DESCRIPTION
The Bot provides automatic notifications in Discord servers for new YouTube uploads and Twitch live streams from specified channels.

2. USAGE
You may use the Bot for personal, community, or organizational Discord servers in accordance with Discordâ€™s Terms of Service. You agree not to abuse, exploit, reverse-engineer, or redistribute the Bot or its functionality.

3. API USAGE
UploadNotifier uses the YouTube Data API and Twitch API. By using the Bot, you agree to also follow the terms set by these services:
- YouTube API Terms of Service: https://developers.google.com/youtube/terms/api-services-terms-of-service
- Twitch Developer Agreement: https://www.twitch.tv/p/legal/developer-agreement/

4. DATA COLLECTION
UploadNotifier stores minimal configuration data, specifically:
- Discord Server (Guild) ID
- Notification Channel ID
- Optional Role ID for pings
- Tracked YouTube and Twitch channel identifiers and display names

No personal user data (e.g., usernames, messages, DMs) is collected or stored.

